Utility to connect to WPA2 AP in command line
It allows to set up passphrase once. The passphrase is stored in encoded way in a file, so that it is not necessary to enter it again at next connection.

Usage: 
    wpa [-e essid | --essid essid] [-i iface | --iface iface] [-p passphrase | --pass passphrase] [-h | --help]

   -e | --eesid essid name to connect to. If not present, list the available ESSIDs
   -i | --iface interface to use. Defaulting to wlan0
   -p | --pass  WPA passphrase. If not defined, look for a previously defined passphrase for the ESSID
   -h | --help  Display this message and exits


